[[collapsible show="The world's largest Bass Pro Shop (Commentary)" hide="-Close"]]
Come on and slam! This was day 1 of 2021 Jamcon, and was banged out in maybe 5 hours (one of which was spent trying to find a cc-compliant version of the 'women want me, fish fear me' hat unsuccessfully). This came after a month long motivation drought, and I'm pretty happy with it. It's certainly not perfect, but it's a funny premise, a topic I'm passionate about and I enjoyed writing it thoroughly.

I've been told that this is a critique of Middle-Class America and consumerism literally becoming centuries old faith and rituals. I wish I was smart enough to put that in.
[[/collapsible]]
---------------
* [[[SCP-5894 | SCP-5894 - La Luz de Yara]]]
[[module ListPages name="scp-5894" category="*" order="created_at desc" limit="1" separate="no"]]
(%%created_at%%) (+%%rating%%), Last comment by %%commented_by%%, %%commented_at%%
[[/module]]
[[collapsible show="This commentary gets serious btw. (Commentary)" hide="-Close"]]
This is an article about Hatuey. Hatuey was a Cacique in Hayti who witnessed the brutality of early Spanish colonialism and fled his home to Cuba, in an attempt to save his own life and rally support to oust the Spanish of Cuba's shores when they arrived. The Taíno of Cuba did not believe that people could act with the barbarity that the Spanish did, and as such did not heed his call by large and were unprepared when the Spanish arrived. Hatuey's resistance failed, and the resulting Spanish atrocities in Cuba I will not mention here. 

This is an article paying respect to the first hero of 300 years of Cuban resistance. A man who laid down his life to defend a home that wasn't even his, without whom the Taíno culture would have been destroyed entirely.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]Despite 500 years of repression (that has only very recently slowed own), small Taíno communities survived in the disconnected mountains, often only even getting road connections in the 1960s-70s.[[/span]] I don't believe I've done this concept or figure justice, but I hope you enjoy regardless.
[[/collapsible]]
